definitions.definition: To manipulate something roughly, causing physical damage .
examples: If you mishandle a fragile package, the contents may break.

definitions.definition: To deal with a situation incorrectly or ineffectively ; to make a mistake in handling a situation.
examples: The prime minister was accused of mishandling the diplomatic crisis.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To manipulate something roughly, causing physical damage .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To deal with a situation incorrectly or ineffectively ; to make a mistake in handling a situation.
